Two issues keep the verdict from **safe**:

2. Blockers remaining (must fix before `/goal`)

- **W1 stale / contradictory claim in `determined_state`.** It says `docs/heresy-detectors.md` “is missing H030/H031 rows” <ref_snippet file="/Users/wiz/go-choir/docs/definitions/og-dolt-heresy-completion-2026-07-08.md" lines="378-381"/>, but those rows already exist <ref_snippet file="/Users/wiz/go-choir/docs/heresy-detectors.md" lines="32-33"/>. The same doc’s Phase A W1 and C3 already say to bind the *existing* rows <ref_snippet file="/Users/wiz/go-choir/docs/definitions/og-dolt-heresy-completion-2026-07-08.md" lines="524-532"/>. This stale executable state can mislead an agent into re-creating or duplicating detector rows. Fix: rewrite the `determined_state` claim and W1 wording to “manifest exists with H030/H031 rows; missing items are `scripts/check-heresies.sh` and the CI discovery job.”

3. Important issues remaining (should fix before Phase A)

- **Archived `docs/archive/heresy-eradication-2026-07-07.md` still contains historical `/goal` strings and unarchived paths.** It still has `/goal docs/definitions/heresy-eradication-2026-07-07.md` <ref_snippet file="/Users/wiz/go-choir/docs/archive/heresy-eradication-2026-07-07.md" lines="10-12"/> <ref_snippet file="/Users/wiz/go-choir/docs/archive/heresy-eradication-2026-07-07.md" lines="410-421"/> and `docs/mission-og-dolt-heresy-hard-cutover-v0.md` references <ref_snippet file="/Users/wiz/go-choir/docs/archive/heresy-eradication-2026-07-07.md" lines="32-34"/> <ref_snippet file="/Users/wiz/go-choir/docs/archive/heresy-eradication-2026-07-07.md" lines="338-339"/> <ref_snippet file="/Users/wiz/go-choir/docs/archive/heresy-eradication-2026-07-07.md" lines="412-414"/>. The redirect note at the top is load-bearing <ref_snippet file="/Users/wiz/go-choir/docs/archive/heresy-eradication-2026-07-07.md" lines="1-4"/>, but these stale executable strings and unarchived paths are a footgun in source material the current mission imports. Fix: annotate them as historical/non-authoritative or repoint to `docs/archive/...` and the umbrella definition.

- **Code reality checks match the doc, but execution must not get ahead of the doc.** `internal/proxy/route_resolver.go` still falls back to hard-coded VM IDs <ref_snippet file="/Users/wiz/go-choir/internal/proxy/route_resolver.go" lines="38-47"/>, `internal/vmctl/client.go:22` still has 180s default timeout <ref_snippet file="/Users/wiz/go-choir/internal/vmctl/client.go" lines="20-23"/>, `internal/proxy/handlers.go:46` has a 10s retry window <ref_snippet file="/Users/wiz/go-choir/internal/proxy/handlers.go" lines="44-49"/>, and `internal/server/server.go` creates an `http.Server` with no `ReadTimeout`/`WriteTimeout` <ref_snippet file="/Users/wiz/go-choir/internal/server/server.go" lines="71-92"/>. The doc correctly records these as violations and scopes them as Phase A (W2) and Phase D (H031) work, so they are not doc-readiness blockers, but they are the real red-class work the Phase A gate must prove.

4. Minor issues / nits

- `docs/definitions/og-dolt-heresy-completion-2026-07-08.md` line 524 says “extend the existing `docs/heresy-detectors.md` manifest with H030/H031 banned-pattern rows”; since those rows already exist, this should be rephrased to “bind the existing H030/H031 rows into the CI detector job.”
- Phase Gate Protocol line 498 still parenthetically says “(Phases C, D, E)” for red-class gates; Phase A is explicitly red-class at lines 518-522, so the parenthetical could be generalized to avoid misread.
- `docs/mission-graph.yaml` has duplicate node IDs (with/without path/ledger) as pre-existing graph debt; the required superseded nodes for the archived docs are present.
- `internal/computerversion/dolt_promotion_adapter.go` comment at lines 18-22 still states the 2026-07-07 “sql-server required” conclusion; the doc correctly scopes updating this to the Phase A pinned-connection test result, so this is expected, not a doc blocker.
- `docs/evidence/agentic-consensus-2026-07-08-mission-readiness-recheck-2/` is untracked; commit or remove before stopping.

5. Confidence: **medium**

The document is structurally coherent and most of the residual blockers are closed, but one stale executable state claim (W1) and stale executable strings in an imported archive doc keep it from a **safe** /goal verdict. Once those two doc-truth issues are fixed, this should be ready to execute.
